## Evaluated and Rejected (this run)
- bincode (Rust): 207.8M downloads, RUSTSEC-2025-0141 — wincode provides wire-compatible v1 drop-in with 3 security audits, postcard is community-preferred migration (6.2M recent). Gap narrowing.
- heck (Rust): 780M total, 135M recent — has 2nd maintainer (jplatte), last release Mar 2024. Not strongly abandoned.
- mime (Rust): 380M total, 57M recent — seanmonstar still active in ecosystem (hyper/reqwest).
- foreign-types (Rust): 274M total, 38M recent, 6yr stale — very niche FFI macro framework, hard adoption.
- scopeguard (Rust): 580M total, 93M recent — tiny scope (~100 lines), not worth a project.
- ppv-lite86 (Rust): 559M total — specialized SIMD crypto, extremely hard to implement correctly.
- node-fetch (Node): 105M/wk — native fetch exists in Node 21+, CJS-only use case is backward.
- inflight, xtend, through, performance-now, caseless, tunnel-agent, concat-stream (Node): all legacy transitive deps of deprecated request ecosystem.
- q (Node): 11.4M/wk, archived — native Promise replaces it.
- tinycolor2 fork (@ctrl/tinycolor): compromised, not safe.
- rsa (Python): 401M/mo — already replaced by ciphertrust.
- httplib2 + google-auth-httplib2 (Python): 119M/mo — locked into Google API client, solution is Google migrating.
- py (Python): 61M/mo — pytest migrating to pathlib.

